    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="87"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                            type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d87fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attach, London, via
                        the White House Map Room and Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">operational priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde Park</hi>
                        </placeName>?] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-02">2 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 406, personal and secret, for the <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1"
                        >Former Naval Person</gloss> from the President.</p>
                <p>For many reasons it is advisable that <persName corresp="#p_HC1"
                        >Cordell</persName> be back in Washington while I am away and even now he
                    can be home by the 13th.</p>
                <p>For escort reasons also it will be much easier to carry through the original plan
                    and a change would interfere with convoys. If I leave by 14th at latest and by
                    going straight through I ought to be able to meet you and staffs in Cairo by the
                    22nd or 23rd. Perhaps it is just as well to get the main business over first,
                    and you and I can do the inspection work on the way back.</p>
                <p>I am wiring <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName> to ask <gloss
                        target="#t_UJ1">U. J.</gloss> if he could come to Basra for even one day.
                    That would be infinitely better than no meeting with him at all.</p>
                <p>I will let you know as soon as I hear.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
